result.execSummary:
The defendant Aaron Timothy Wolk was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Resisting/Failing to Stop/Fleeing, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(2t).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

11:29 Defendant Aaron Timothy Wolk in court with attorney Donald J. Schwab.  Rory Eoin O'Sullivan appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 14TR689 heard at this time. OSullivan files an amended information. Files Motion to Dismiss 14TR689. OSullivan guilty to charges contained in the amended information. 2 years probation. Schwab withdraws his NGI plea, Def agrees. Court withdraws NGI plea.  Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form is filed with the court; court reviews with Def.  Constitutional rights explained to defendant.  Exam'd re: understanding of law, penalty and rights. Def was in the armed services. Def pleas guilty to Ct#1 and Ct#2 contained in the amended information; Schwab stipulates to a factual basis.   COURT ACCEPTS PLEA, FINDS DEF FREELY, INTELLIGENTLY, KNOWINGLY & UNDERSTANDINGLY MADE AND WAIVES CONSTITUTIONAL RIGHTS. Court finds and adjudicates Def guilty of Ct#1 and Ct#2 in 14CF147. Dismisses 14TR689. OSullivan and Schwab address sentencing. Schwab requests 2 days credit be put on JOC and 1 year probation. Def addresses the court. Court: S/W 2 years probation conditions; concurrent: court costs and the agent should consider what treatments Def is getting at the VA and maybe maybe those conditions of probation, coordinating a Mentor through the Veteran's Service Office.  Appeal rights are given to the defendant.
Plea/sentencing hearing at 03-03-2015 11:30 am.
